title: A climber has reached the top of a cliff, and is pulling himself over the corner of the edge. Both hands hold the corner and one leg is over it; the other leg pushes off the rock below. The climber is anatomically correct. Below him is a strange abstract sea of architecture and swirling mechanisms. On the right, the sky and the top of the mountain are sunny, natural, and realistic. On the left, the swirling polygonal ocean below is cubist and bizarre.
pid: de302177-abf2-4bbb-85e8-9f513a249da8
